FBIS3-38059 "drsov039_a_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS `CIA Agent' Persona Non Grata LD2802154494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1511 GMT 28 Feb 94 LD2802154494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Andrey Palariya and Vladimir Smelov] [Text] Moscow, 28 Feb -- CIA agent James Morris, who worked in Moscow under the guise of a counsellor at the U.S. embassy, has been declared "persona non grata." An ITAR-TASS correspondent was informed by reliable sources that an official statement about this was made today to U.S. ambassador in Moscow Thomas Pickering. The U.S. spy will leave Moscow within seven days. This was Moscow's reaction to Washington's decision to expel Aleksandr Lysenko, counsellor at the Russian embassy, from the United States.
